# Hunter Harris Music Portfolio - Claude Code Configuration

## Project Overview
This is a premium music portfolio site built with Next.js 15, showcasing Hunter Harris's releases with animated gradients, parallax effects, and streaming platform integration.

## Tech Stack
- **Framework**: Next.js 15 (App Router)
- **Language**: TypeScript
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS 3.4
- **Animation**: Framer Motion 11
- **Color Extraction**: node-vibrant
- **Font**: Inter (Google Fonts)

## Development Commands
- `npm run dev` - Start development server on http://localhost:3000
- `npm run build` - Build for production (runs color extraction first)
- `npm run start` - Start production server
- `npm run prebuild` - Manually run color extraction script
- `npm run lint` - Run ESLint

## Project Structure
```
app/              - Next.js app directory (pages, layouts, styles)
components/       - React components (reusable UI)
lib/              - Data, types, and utilities
scripts/          - Build scripts (color extraction)
public/artwork/   - Album artwork images
```

## Key Files to Edit
- **lib/releases.ts** - Main data file for releases (EDIT THIS to add/remove releases)
- **app/page.tsx** - Main page component (update social links here)
- **app/layout.tsx** - SEO metadata and fonts
- **app/globals.css** - Global styles and animations

## Auto-Generated Files (DO NOT EDIT)
- **lib/releases.generated.ts** - Generated by color extraction script
- **.next/** - Next.js build output

## Adding a New Release
1. Add artwork to `public/artwork/` (square, 800x800px minimum)
2. Edit `lib/releases.ts` and add a new release object
3. Run `npm run prebuild` to extract colors
4. Test with `npm run dev`

## Component Dependencies
- **ReleaseSection** uses: AnimatedGradient, Artwork, StreamingLinks
- **Page** uses: ReleaseSection, DotNavigation, SocialFooter
- All components are client-side ("use client") except layout

## Styling Conventions
- Mobile-first responsive design
- Tailwind utility classes preferred
- Custom animations in globals.css
- Color tokens defined as CSS variables

## Performance Considerations
- First release artwork has `priority` prop for LCP optimization
- All other images lazy-load automatically
- Gradient animations use GPU-accelerated transforms
- Reduced motion support via prefers-reduced-motion

## Accessibility Features
- Semantic HTML (main, section, nav, footer)
- ARIA labels on all interactive elements
- Keyboard navigation support
- Focus visible states
- Reduced motion support

## Color Extraction Process
The `scripts/generate-palettes.ts` script:
1. Reads artwork from `public/artwork/`
2. Extracts 7 colors using node-vibrant
3. Generates `lib/releases.generated.ts`
4. Runs automatically before production builds

