## Deployment
- **Recommended**: Vercel (auto-detects Next.js)
- **Alternatives**: Netlify, AWS Amplify, Cloudflare Pages
- The prebuild script runs automatically during deployment

## Browser Support
- Modern browsers (Chrome, Firefox, Safari, Edge - latest 2 versions)
- iOS Safari 14+
- Chrome Android 90+

## Troubleshooting

### Colors not extracting
- Check artwork files exist in `public/artwork/`
- Verify paths in `lib/releases.ts` match actual files
- Run `npm run prebuild` manually

### Build errors
- Run `npm install` to ensure all dependencies are installed
- Check for TypeScript errors with `npm run lint`

### Images not loading
- Verify `artworkPath` matches actual file in `public/artwork/`
- Check file extensions (.jpg, .png, .svg)

## Code Style
- TypeScript strict mode enabled
- ESLint with Next.js config
- Prettier not configured (use editor defaults)
- Use interfaces over types for objects
- Prefer functional components with hooks

## Animation Guidelines
- Use Framer Motion for scroll-triggered animations
- CSS animations for continuous effects (gradients)
- Respect prefers-reduced-motion
- Keep animations subtle (400-600ms duration)

## Image Guidelines
- Artwork: Square (1:1), minimum 800x800px
- Format: JPG for photos, PNG for transparency
- Compress before adding (<500KB recommended)
- Use descriptive filenames (e.g., "album-name.jpg")

## Data Model
See `lib/types.ts` for full interfaces:
- **Release**: Main release data structure
- **ColorPalette**: 7 colors extracted from artwork
- **StreamingLinks**: Platform URLs (Spotify, Apple Music, YouTube Music)

